@1:07 - I do have tips on hitchhiking in India ( ateast in Tamil Nadu ). Ask for a lift (hitchhiking is called lift in many places ) from a place with less traffic and preferably no public transport. The rarer the vehicles the better your chances. 

The drivers are sympathetic when there is no one around as they believe it is their responsibility to help. If there is lot of traffic every driver will believe someone else will help and at the end no one helps.

This is commonly known as "Bystander effect" but applies here as well
